{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"6337","heading":"Critical technology partnerships and cooperative research and development centers","label":"6337 Critical technology partnerships and cooperative research and development centers","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/stA/ptVI/sptB/ch608/schII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextExecutive Order No. 12344, referred to in subsec. (c)(4), is set out as a note under .section 6102 of this title","Prior ProvisionsProvisions similar to those in this section were contained in , War and National Defense, prior to repeal by .section 2794 of Title 50Pub. L. 119–60, § 3111(b)(1)","Amendments2025—, realigned margins.Pub. L. 119–60, § 3111(d)(2)(B)"],"amendments":["Amendments2025—, realigned margins.Pub. L. 119–60, § 3111(d)(2)(B)"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Partnerships","label":"a .—Partnerships","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"For the purpose of facilitating the transfer of technology, the Secretary of Energy shall ensure, to the maximum extent practicable, that research on and development of dual-use critical technology carried out through atomic energy defense activities is conducted through cooperative research and development agreements, or other arrangements, that involve laboratories of the Department of Energy and other entities.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Cooperative Research and Development Centers","label":"b .—Cooperative Research and Development Centers","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Subject to the availability of appropriations provided for such purpose, the Administrator shall establish a cooperative research and development center described in paragraph (2) at each national security laboratory.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A cooperative research and development center described in this paragraph is a center to foster collaborative scientific research, technology development, and the appropriate transfer of research and technology to users in addition to the national security laboratories.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/b/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fb%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"shall enter into cooperative research and development agreements with governmental, public, academic, or private entities; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/b/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fb%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"may enter into a contract with respect to constructing, purchasing, managing, or leasing buildings or other facilities.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Definitions","label":"c .—Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fc%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"that is critical to atomic energy defense activities, as determined by the Secretary of Energy;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fc%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"that has military applications and nonmilitary applications; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fc%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"that is a defense critical technology (as defined in section 4801).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “cooperative research and development agreement” has the meaning given that term by section 12(d) of the Stevenson-Wydler Technology Innovation Act of 1980 ().15 U.S.C. 3710a(d)","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fc%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"firms, or a consortium of firms, that are eligible to participate in a partnership or other arrangement with a laboratory of the Department of Energy, as determined in accordance with applicable law and regulations; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fc%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/3/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fc%2F3%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Institutions of higher education in the United States.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/3/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fc%2F3%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Departments and agencies of the Federal Government other than the Department of Energy.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/3/B/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fc%2F3%2FB%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Agencies of State governments.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iv","heading":null,"label":"iv","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/3/B/iv","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fc%2F3%2FB%2Fiv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Any other persons or entities that may be eligible and appropriate, as determined in accordance with applicable laws and regulations.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6337/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs6337%2Fc%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “atomic energy defense activities” does not include activities covered by Executive Order No. 12344, dated , pertaining to the Naval nuclear propulsion program.February 1, 1982","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
